definitions.definition: Opening of an organ by its own means (such as an anther or a seed pod ) to release its contents.
A rupture , as with a surgical wound opening up, often with a flow of serous fluid.
Opening, gaping , in a general sense.

main_definition: ( botany ) Opening of an organ by its own means (such as an anther or a seed pod ) to release its contents.
secondary_definitions: ( medicine ) A rupture , as with a surgical wound opening up, often with a flow of serous fluid.
( rare ) Opening, gaping , in a general sense.
